cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the design of a MAC protocol for cognitive radio networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses spectrum sensing and access, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Cognitive radio networks have security concerns, and the paper may discuss security aspects of the proposed MAC protocol. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may discuss control aspects of the proposed MAC protocol, such as how to coordinate spectrum access among multiple cognitive radio users. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Cognitive radio networks can be used for multimedia applications, and the paper may discuss how the proposed MAC protocol can improve the performance of such applications.
